class MLP(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size, output_size, dropout_rate=0.5):
        super(MLP, self).__init__()
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(input_size, hidden_size)
        self.relu = nn.ReLU()
        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(dropout_rate)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(hidden_size, output_size)
        self.sigmoid = nn.Sigmoid()
    def forward(self, x):
        out = self.fc1(x)
        out = self.relu(out)
        out = self.dropout(out)
        out = self.fc2(out)
        out = self.sigmoid(out)
        return out  

# Initialize MLP
input_size = X_train_pca.shape[1]  # After PCA transformation
hidden_size = 64
output_size = 1

# Wrap MLP in Skorch for Scikit-learn 
net = NeuralNetClassifier(
    module=MLP,
    module__input_size=input_size,
    module__hidden_size=hidden_size,
    module__output_size=output_size,
    module__dropout_rate=0.5,
    criterion=nn.BCELoss,
    optimizer=optim.Adam,
    max_epochs=20,
    lr=0.001,
    batch_size=32,
    train_split=None,
)


# Trainning

Best MLP Model after experimenting with layers,weight decay, learning rate, etc¶

class MLP(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size1, hidden_size2, hidden_size3, output_size, dropout_rate=0.5):
        super(MLP, self).__init__()
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(input_size, hidden_size1)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(hidden_size1, hidden_size2)
        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(hidden_size2, hidden_size3)
        self.fc4 = nn.Linear(hidden_size3, output_size)
        self.relu = nn.ReLU()
        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(dropout_rate)
        self.sigmoid = nn.Sigmoid()

    def forward(self, x):
        out = self.fc1(x)
        out = self.relu(out)
        out = self.dropout(out)
        out = self.fc2(out)
        out = self.relu(out)
        out = self.dropout(out)
        out = self.fc3(out)
        out = self.relu(out)
        out = self.dropout(out)
        out = self.fc4(out)
        out = self.sigmoid(out)
        return out

# MLP Hyperparameter Tuning
mlp_param_grid = {
    'module__hidden_size1': [64, 128],  
    'module__hidden_size2': [32, 64], 
    'module__hidden_size3': [16, 32],  
    'module__dropout_rate': [0.3, 0.5],  
    'lr': [0.001, 0.01],  
    'max_epochs': [30, 40],  
    'optimizer__weight_decay': [0.0001, 0.001]  
}

mlp_grid_search = GridSearchCV(
    NeuralNetClassifier(
        module=MLP,
        module__input_size=X_train_pca.shape[1],
        module__output_size=1,
        optimizer=optim.Adam,
        criterion=nn.BCELoss,
        train_split=None,
        verbose=0
    ),
    param_grid=mlp_param_grid,
    scoring='f1',
    cv=3,  # 3-fold cross-validation
    n_jobs=-1  
)

# Fit MLP grid search to find the best parameters
mlp_grid_search.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_resampled)

print("Best MLP Parameters:", mlp_grid_search.best_params_)
print("Best MLP F1 Score:", mlp_grid_search.best_score_)

# Train MLP with best parameters
best_mlp = mlp_grid_search.best_estimator_
best_mlp.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_resampled)

import time
start_time = time.time()
best_mlp.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_resampled)
mlp_training_time = time.time() - start_time

print(f"MLP Training Time: {mlp_training_time:.2f} seconds")

class MLP(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size1, hidden_size2, hidden_size3, output_size, dropout_rate=0.5):
        super(MLP, self).__init__()
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(input_size, hidden_size1)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(hidden_size1, hidden_size2)
        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(hidden_size2, hidden_size3)
        self.fc4 = nn.Linear(hidden_size3, output_size)
        self.relu = nn.ReLU()
        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(dropout_rate)
        self.sigmoid = nn.Sigmoid()

    def forward(self, x):
        out = self.fc1(x)
        out = self.relu(out)
        out = self.dropout(out)
        out = self.fc2(out)
        out = self.relu(out)
        out = self.dropout(out)
        out = self.fc3(out)
        out = self.relu(out)
        out = self.dropout(out)
        out = self.fc4(out)
        out = self.sigmoid(out)
        return out

    scoring='f1',

}, inplace=True)

# Add color to the accuracy column

    color = 'blue' if val > 0.95 else 'green' if val > 0.90 else 'orange' if val > 0.80 else 'red'
    return f'background-color: {color}'

    'F1-Score': f1_score(y_val, y_val_pred_svm_adjusted),

}

def plot_roc_curves(X, y, dataset_name, ax):
    mlp_proba = best_mlp.predict_proba(X)[:, 1]
    svm_proba = best_svm.predict_proba(X)[:, 1]
    
    # Calculate ROC curves
    fpr_mlp, tpr_mlp, _ = roc_curve(y, mlp_proba)
    fpr_svm, tpr_svm, _ = roc_curve(y, svm_proba)
    
    # Calculate AUC scores
    roc_auc_mlp = auc(fpr_mlp, tpr_mlp)
    roc_auc_svm = auc(fpr_svm, tpr_svm)
    
    # Plot ROC curves
    ax.plot(fpr_mlp, tpr_mlp, color='blue', linestyle='-', 
            label=f'MLP (AUC = {roc_auc_mlp:.2f})')
    ax.plot(fpr_svm, tpr_svm, color='red', linestyle='-', 
            label=f'SVM (AUC = {roc_auc_svm:.2f})')
    
    # Plot random guessing line
    ax.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='gray', linestyle='--')
    
    ax.set_xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    ax.set_xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    ax.set_ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    ax.set_title(f'ROC Curves - {dataset_name} Dataset')
    ax.legend(loc="lower right")

fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 16))

plot_roc_curves(X_train_pca, y_train_resampled, "Training", axes[0, 0])
plot_roc_curves(X_val_pca, y_val, "Validation", axes[0, 1])
plot_roc_curves(X_test_pca, y_test, "Test", axes[1, 0])
plot_roc_curves(X_all_pca, y_all, "All Data", axes[1, 1])

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
